downloadTitle: Update for Windows Internal Database x64 (WYukon SP2 x64)
downloadDescription: Windows Internal database is a relational data store for Windows roles and features only, such as Windows SharePoint Services and Windows Server Update Services.
detailsSection: This update upgrades Windows Internal Database used by Windows components such as Windows SharePoint Services and Windows Server Update Services.
systemRequirementsSection: This update is available only on Windows 2003.
installInstructionSection:
Please click the download button to download the Windows Internal Database x64 setup package for Windows Server 2003 OS.

For a new install of the Windows Internal Database when it does not exist already:
msiexec /i SSEE_10.msi CALLERID=OCSetup.exe /qn REBOOT=ReallySupress /l*v [logfilepath]

To upgrade an existing lower version of the Windows Internal Database:
msiexec /i SSEE_10.msi CALLERID=OCSetup.exe REINSTALL=ALL REINSTALLMODE=vomus /qn REBOOT=ReallySupress /l*v [logfile]

To completely uninstall the Windows Internal Database:
start /wait msiexec /x {BDD79957-5801-4A2D-B09E-852E7FA64D01} CALLERID=OCSetup.exe /qn REBOOT=ReallySupress /l*v [logfile]
